\hypertarget{introduction}{%
\section{\texorpdfstring{Introduction\protect\hyperlink{introduction}{}}{Introduction}}\label{introduction}}

This proposal is part of a group of papers aimed at improving the state
of Freestanding. It marks (parts of) \VERB|\NormalTok{std::array}|,
\VERB|\NormalTok{std::string\_view}|, \VERB|\NormalTok{std::variant}|,
and \VERB|\NormalTok{std::optional}| as such. A future paper might add
\VERB|\NormalTok{std::bitset}| (as was the original goal in
{[}\protect\hyperlink{ref-P2268R0}{P2268R0}{]}

\hypertarget{motivation-and-scope}{%
\section{\texorpdfstring{Motivation and
Scope\protect\hyperlink{motivation-and-scope}{}}{Motivation and Scope}}\label{motivation-and-scope}}

All of the aforementioned classes are fundamentally compatible with
Freestanding, except for a few methods that throw
(e.g.~\VERB|\NormalTok{array::at}|). We explicitly
\VERB|\NormalTok{=delete}| these undesirable methods.

We are proposing to add all these classes because they are fundamental
in modern, day-to-day C++.

